</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SCD vs LSoEE for offhand</span><hr size=1> um... no matter what delay you have, backstab will always refresh at 10 seconds with no haste.<br>
<br>
With max haste at 55, backstab refreshes at 4 seconds with max haste<br>
<br>
<br>
Dont believe me? i dont understand that, it has been this way since the game came out, and if you have ever played a rogue then you would know i'm telling the truth.<br>
<br>
you honestly havent ever noticed backstab is always the same wether you have a 17 or 30 delay weapon?<br>
<br>
This is like asking me to prove that offhand is independent of mainhand delay... you just have to go in game and test it out yourself<br>
<br>
EDITed portion:<br>
Ok, first off, some other rogue back me up on this to convince him.<br>
<br>
Secondly, Haste does not affect (you said effect, btw) delay, it affects the number of attacks you get in any given period, which indirectly affects delay.<br>
<br>
anyway, ratio is NOT all that matters for main hand.<br>
<br>
You have to deal with A) backstab damage and B) main hand damage bonus.<br>
<br>
faster weapons will do more damage because of main hand damage bonus that is applied every attack. higher dmg weapons will affect backstab damage, and thus overall damage by a great deal.<br>
<br>
its a balance of speed vs dmg.<br>
<br>
even though 13/20 and 15/25 parse out to the same damage, the % of pierce and % of backstab will change dramatically.<br>
<br>
right now, assuming max haste and a 15 delay weapon, every level 60 rogue will do the same amount of backstab damage over any period of time.<br>
<br>
This is one reason i, and many rogue's are mad at verant. Both for the no 15+ dmg weapon rule, and for the max haste cap.<br>
<br>
Because this means from now on, the only way they can bump up rogue damage, is make 15/18, 15/16 ect weapons, because backstab damage is now a constant that can be applied to the damage equation.<br>
<br>
I'd like to see some special weapons, like have something like +300 damage max to backstab damage. because right now, uber rogue's cant increase the damage they do by backstab, than any rogue with an epic.<br>
<br>
that, or re-work the backstab formula to make 16 damage weapons a feasable alternative. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udrakinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drakinn</A> at: 1/2/02 6:15:17 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udagurrinch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dagurr Inch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/2/02 6:54:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12322.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dagurr.homestead.com/files/images/GrinchHand.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SCD vs LSoEE for offhand</span><hr size=1> Wading through the condescension... thanx.<br>
